### Get your documents witnessed in front of a notary public

Download an [‘Affidavit/Affirmation’ form](https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/affirmationaffidavit-of-marital-status-form) and a [‘Notice of Marriage’ form](https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/notice-of-marriage-form--2) and take them with you to a notary public.

### Get your documents witnessed at the embassy

[Make an appointment at the embassy in Sofia.](https://www.consular-appointments.service.gov.uk/fco/#!/british-embassy-sofia/notice-of-marriage-or-civil-partnership/slot_picker)

You’ll need to complete an [‘Affidavit/Affirmation’ form](https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/affirmationaffidavit-of-marital-status-form) and a [‘Notice of Marriage’ form](https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/notice-of-marriage-form--2).

You can download and fill in (but not sign) the forms in advance.

You must take the forms with you to your appointment.
